<page>
   <topic>SQL_DATE Function</topic>
   <syntax>Formatted_Date as C = SQL_Date(* date [,N option [,N option2 ]])</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>Formatted_Date</name>
         <description>A formatted date string.</description>
     </argument>
     <argument>
         <name>date</name>
         <description>A date value.</description>
     </argument>
     <argument>
         <name>option</name>
         <description>Numeric</description>
     </argument>
     <argument>
         <name>option2</name>
         <description>Numeric</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>
   <description>Takes a date or time value and returns a character date or date-time string using the format for Alpha Portable SQL - {yyyy-mm-dd}</description>
   <discussion>
The SQL_DATE() function generates a character string with the format: {YYYY-MM-DD}.
   </discussion>
   <example><![CDATA[
? sql_date(date() )
= "{2006-03-22}"

]]></example>
   
   <see>
      <ref>SQL Helper Functions</ref>
      <ref>Date and Time Functions</ref>
   </see>
 
 
